title: Occult - Magical Ritual Methods (pdf) EarthBow
description:
Gray, William - Magical Ritual Methods, 1971, 301 pages

The reader learns about proper grounding and centering, constructing workable psychic shielding, the use of sound in chants and rites, and the proper construction and use of ritual tools. The various parts of a working rite of Magick are explained in enough detail to be of practical use to the student or practitioner.


Note: I will be adding many more titles soon, Search for "EarthBow" for a list of available titles.

As always, comments (good or bad) are appreciated

Keywords: occult, ritual, esoteric, magik, magick, witchcraft
